---
title: "Klock Quartet"
---

![Klock Quartet perfoming at the University of Massachusetts Amherst](images/QuartetPhoto.png)

Formed by a group of dedicated music professionals who met during their undergraduate studies at the University of Massachusetts Amherst, the Klock Quartet is a passionate ensemble celebrating the versatility of the saxophone. Under the guidance of renowned professor Lynn Klock, the members developed a deep musical connection that continues to thrive today.

The quartet has recently showcased their talent at the Saxophone Symposium at the University of Massachusetts Amherst, the University of Denver, Colorado, as well as weddings, and local schools, bringing a unique blend of styles and rich harmonies to every performance. Committed to sharing their love for music, the Klock Quartet aims to create memorable experiences through their artistry and collaboration.
